a landline?

511
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:51,818
Is it local?

512
00:20:52,018 --> 00:20:53,320
It's an emergency.

513
00:20:57,857 --> 00:20:59,792
Come on, Ali.
[busy signal beeping]

514
00:20:59,992 --> 00:21:01,027
Damn it.

515
00:21:02,862 --> 00:21:04,697
[Line rings]

516
00:21:04,897 --> 00:21:06,999
Our seismologists
will be reviewing

517
00:21:07,199 --> 00:21:08,501
The data more thoroughly,
[telephone ringing]

518
00:21:08,701 --> 00:21:09,602
But at this time,

519
00:21:09,802 --> 00:21:11,003
We estimate it to be...

520
00:21:11,203 --> 00:21:12,639
Caltech Geological Survey.
This is...

521
00:21:12,839 --> 00:21:13,773
Chet,
it's Molly Dunn.

522
00:21:13,973 --> 00:21:16,676
Oh, hey, Molly.
You okay?

523
00:21:16,876 --> 00:21:18,811
I heard
that last quake hit
a little close to you.

524
00:21:19,879 --> 00:21:21,781
Cell towers
are going down,

525
00:21:22,682 --> 00:21:23,683
And I don't know
the next time

526
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:25,184
I'll be able to get
to a landline or how
long they'll last,

527
00:21:26,052 --> 00:21:26,786
So you have
to listen to me.

528
00:21:27,820 --> 00:21:29,322
We have got to enact
a level-four evac.

529
00:21:29,522 --> 00:21:31,358
This is
going to be big,

530
00:21:31,558 --> 00:21:33,360
Upwards of a M10,
Chet!

531
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,395
Molly, Molly, please.

532
00:21:35,595 --> 00:21:38,465
My system works, Chet.
It knew about Malibu

533
00:21:38,665 --> 00:21:40,433
Four minutes
before it happened.

534
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:41,868
Molly...
And now I'm showing

535
00:21:43,169 --> 00:21:44,637
No fewer
than 18 right lateral
strike-slip warnings

536
00:21:44,837 --> 00:21:46,305
On 19 of my units

537
00:21:47,607 --> 00:21:49,576
Up and down
all 800 miles of
the San Andreas, Chet.

538
00:21:49,776 --> 00:21:51,744
Yeah, and in 2008,
you said the same thing.

539
00:21:51,944 --> 00:21:53,813
Only, it turned out
to be dune buggies
and high wind.

540
00:21:54,013 --> 00:21:55,848
That was eight million
lines of code,

541
00:21:56,048 --> 00:21:57,584
Chet, your code!

542
00:21:57,784 --> 00:21:59,619
These are new rigs,
new code,

543
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:00,920
And it's working!

544
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,855
A level-four evac, Molly?

545
00:22:03,055 --> 00:22:05,358
You have any idea
what I'd have to do?

546
00:22:05,558 --> 00:22:08,027
Will you just look
at my data? Please?

547
00:22:09,095 --> 00:22:10,563
All right, fine.

548
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:12,732
Send it over to me.
I'll take a look at it.

549
00:22:12,932 --> 00:22:14,434
I did! Check your inbox.

550
00:22:15,802 --> 00:22:16,536
We have got
to pull the trigger
on this evac protocol.

551
00:22:17,637 --> 00:22:19,005
You want me to evacuate
13 million people

552
00:22:20,206 --> 00:22:21,741
Because your science project
made a lucky guess?

553
00:22:21,941 --> 00:22:23,543
That's not good science.
It's...

554
00:22:23,743 --> 00:22:26,679
An M10, Chet.
Listen to me.

555
00:22:26,879 --> 00:22:28,981
I... I gotta go.

556
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,850
There will be
minor aftershocks,

557
00:22:31,050 --> 00:22:32,251
But if any do occur,

558
00:22:32,452 --> 00:22:35,555
The frequency of these events
should taper off quickly.

559
00:22:35,755 --> 00:22:37,590
[Slams receiver]
Damn it.

560
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,870
Oh, no, no, no!

561
00:22:51,070 --> 00:22:51,971
Professor Dunn?
Shit.

562
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:53,906
Nick, I'm sorry
about earlier,

563
00:22:54,841 --> 00:22:55,675
And I'm sorry
about the grade,

564
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:56,943
But I really don't have
time for this right now.

565
00:22:57,710 --> 00:22:57,777
No, no. How's Ali?
Huh?

566
00:22:58,411 --> 00:22:59,512
Ali. Is she okay?

567
00:23:00,146 --> 00:23:00,547
Yeah, she's fine.

568
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:01,714
I can't
get ahold of her.

569
00:23:02,582 --> 00:23:02,882
Did she leave
the hotel yet?

570
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:05,585
She's so stubborn.

571
00:23:05,785 --> 00:23:07,854
You're Ali's boyfriend.

572
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:09,489
I wanted to be
up-front about it.

573
00:23:09,689 --> 00:23:10,890
She made me swear
not to tell.

574
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:12,625
She said
you'd disapprove.

575
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:15,127
Yeah, she's right.
Excuse me.

576
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:16,395
Are you gonna
go get her?

577
00:23:16,596 --> 00:23:17,630
I am.

578
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,566
You need a car, right?

579
00:23:19,766 --> 00:23:21,400
Yes, I will.

580
00:23:21,601 --> 00:23:23,436
We can use mine.
"We"?

581
00:23:23,636 --> 00:23:24,904
Or I can go on my own.

582
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:27,607
If you think you can
get there before me,
be my guest.

583
00:23:28,741 --> 00:23:29,842
All right,
where's your car?

584
00:23:30,042 --> 00:23:31,444
Over here.

585
00:23:35,582 --> 00:23:36,783
Oh, you can't
be serious.

586
00:23:36,983 --> 00:23:38,117
She'll get us there.

587
00:23:42,154 --> 00:23:43,590
All right. Take PCH.

588
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:45,825
We should stay off
the elevated freeways.

589
00:23:53,733 --> 00:23:54,934
Uh...

590
00:23:55,134 --> 00:23:56,536
Yeah, just go.

591
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:13,986
[Sirens blaring]

592
00:24:17,323 --> 00:24:19,792
Lobby looks good.
I see no damage here,

593
00:24:19,992 --> 00:24:22,495
Not even a crack.
Meet me in the ballroom.

594
00:24:22,695 --> 00:24:25,565
Uh, that was
quite a little shaker
we had there.

595
00:24:25,765 --> 00:24:27,767
Um, is everything
looking okay? I mean...

596
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:29,502
Yeah, that's actually
pretty old.

597
00:24:29,702 --> 00:24:30,637
It's nothing new.

598
00:24:31,538 --> 00:24:31,904
Everything's
checking out fine.

599
00:24:34,941 --> 00:24:36,976
Whoo-hoo! [Chuckles]

600
00:24:38,711 --> 00:24:41,113
Oh, the technology today.

601
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:45,818
When I was a kid,
it was a real luxury
to have your picture taken.

602
00:24:46,018 --> 00:24:51,824
I've had more pictures taken
in the last five years
than my entire life.

603
00:24:52,024 --> 00:24:53,092
Say cheese.

604
00:24:54,393 --> 00:24:55,795
You'll send that to us?

605
00:24:55,995 --> 00:24:56,963
Of course.

606
00:24:58,397 --> 00:25:00,700
Oh, is dear
Mr. Dittmann around?

607
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,168
No, at a conference,

608
00:25:03,402 --> 00:25:05,638
But I'm sure
he'll be happy
to see you tomorrow.

609
00:25:05,838 --> 00:25:06,639
Wonderful.

610
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:15,247
I'll radio you when
the dim sum's here.

611
00:25:15,447 --> 00:25:16,683
Okay.

612
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:19,552
Is this thing safe
so soon after a quake?

613
00:25:19,752 --> 00:25:22,254
Sure thing. It's
been retrofitted
up to an 8.0.

614
00:25:22,454 --> 00:25:25,558
All right, well,
too out of shape
to take the stairs then.

615
00:25:25,758 --> 00:25:27,594
All right. 14th floor.

616
00:25:27,794 --> 00:25:29,896
I hope this thing
can make it.

617
00:25:30,096 --> 00:25:31,163
Oh, it's perfectly safe.

618
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:43,910
Okay. Uh, Hank, Ali,

619
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:45,845
I've tried
calling and texting,

620
00:25:46,045 --> 00:25:47,914
And this is
the only other way

621
00:25:48,114 --> 00:25:50,182
I could think to get
a message to you both.

622
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,051
2,000 hideous,
fake, metal palm trees

623
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,321
Disguised as cell towers
all over the entire
Los Angeles area,

624
00:25:55,521 --> 00:25:58,024
And I can't even make
a single phone call.

625
00:25:58,224 --> 00:25:59,926
All right.
Well, here's the plan.

626
00:26:00,126 --> 00:26:01,260
I'm coming downtown.

627
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:03,029
Ali, I know about Nick,

628
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:05,765
And he's with me
coming to get you.

629
00:26:06,933 --> 00:26:09,001
We just got a glimpse
from up high

630
00:26:09,201 --> 00:26:10,970
Of the entire
San Gabriel basin,

631
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:13,973
And there are
fires and smoke

632
00:26:14,173 --> 00:26:15,174
And helicopters.

633
00:26:15,374 --> 00:26:16,809
Angry people panicked.

634
00:26:18,044 --> 00:26:20,046
Ali, if you're getting this,
please just stay put.

635
00:26:20,246 --> 00:26:22,314
Stay in the hotel.

636
00:26:22,514 --> 00:26:23,315
It looks like the duration

637
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:24,851
Between foreshocks
is decreasing,

638
00:26:25,818 --> 00:26:26,853
Which means
that The Big, Big One

639
00:26:28,254 --> 00:26:29,956
Might actually hit sooner than
my prediction model suggested.

640
00:26:30,156 --> 00:26:31,891
I can't be sure
until I get

641
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:34,093
Some sort of GPS or cellular
to cross-reference

642
00:26:34,293 --> 00:26:35,695
The seismic
or the geological data

643
00:26:36,863 --> 00:26:37,964
From all the sources
on and off the continent,

644
00:26:39,131 --> 00:26:40,332
But forget about all that.
Just stay put, Ali.

645
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:42,268
If you're getting this,
stay put.

646
00:26:43,002 --> 00:26:44,070
We're coming to get you.

647
00:26:45,037 --> 00:26:46,605
It is getting
very crazy out here.

648
00:26:58,851 --> 00:27:01,253
[Beeps]

649
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:04,156
According to this,
we're about to have
another minor trembler.

650
00:27:04,356 --> 00:27:05,357
What's minor?

651
00:27:05,557 --> 00:27:06,926
M3 or 4.

652
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:09,228
We might not even feel it,
though, in a moving...

653
00:27:25,377 --> 00:27:28,114
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

654
00:27:34,253 --> 00:27:37,656
[Tires squeal]

655
00:27:41,493 --> 00:27:43,763
[Screaming]

656
00:27:55,174 --> 00:27:58,144
[Panting]

657
00:28:01,948 --> 00:28:03,049
You okay?

658
00:28:03,249 --> 00:28:04,683
Yeah.

659
00:28:09,488 --> 00:28:11,390
[Engine grinds]

660
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,225
[Warning chimes]
Aw, man.

661
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:24,837
I told you so.
I knew it.

662
00:28:25,037 --> 00:28:26,739
I'm sorry.

663
00:28:26,939 --> 00:28:28,340
All right,
get me out of here.

664
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,076
Don't worry, hon.
Don't worry.

665
00:28:30,276 --> 00:28:32,344
This contraption
has lasted 100 years.

666
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:35,815
That means
it's... it's strong,
not weak.

667
00:28:36,015 --> 00:28:37,016
Ohh! Ahh!

668
00:28:37,216 --> 00:28:37,950
Are you okay,
Mr. Lowenstein?

669
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:40,186
My heart.
Oh, what's wrong?

670
00:28:40,386 --> 00:28:41,788
Sweetheart,
Where's your medication?

671
00:28:41,988 --> 00:28:44,390
Nightstand.
Where do you think?

672
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:46,492
Oh, he left his medicine
on the nightstand.

673
00:28:46,692 --> 00:28:48,861
Why would you
leave it there?

674
00:28:49,061 --> 00:28:49,896
[Groans]
Hello?

675
00:28:50,096 --> 00:28:50,897
Hello?
Anyone there?

676
00:28:51,097 --> 00:28:52,098
Jackson?

677
00:28:53,165 --> 00:28:54,400
God, please get
this door open, please!

678
00:29:10,282 --> 00:29:11,350
Malibu Aviation,

679
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:13,953
This is Bell Four Delta Chaz
requesting landing.

680
00:29:14,153 --> 00:29:15,922
We've been rerouted
due to the earthquake.

681
00:29:16,122 --> 00:29:17,456
Roger that, Bell Four.
Affirmative.

682
00:29:17,656 --> 00:29:19,458
Be advised
it's chaotic down here.

683
00:29:19,658 --> 00:29:20,459
Proceed with caution.

684
00:29:20,659 --> 00:29:22,161
[Beeps]

685
00:29:26,365 --> 00:29:27,499
Minor tremors?

686
00:29:27,699 --> 00:29:28,534
Well, the data's

687
00:29:29,435 --> 00:29:30,136
Hitting me
in fragments, okay?

688
00:29:31,237 --> 00:29:32,004
The entire
infrastructure
must be hosed.

689
00:29:32,839 --> 00:29:33,339
I'm missing
some packets.

690
00:29:34,373 --> 00:29:35,441
Maybe if we're lucky,
we'll get some...

691
00:29:36,475 --> 00:29:37,977
A data signal or
a Wi-Fi or something.

692
00:29:38,177 --> 00:29:40,246
Oh, good.
I could use a latte.

693
00:29:40,446 --> 00:29:41,981
What are we gonna do?

694
00:29:42,181 --> 00:29:43,315
[Sighs]

695
00:29:43,515 --> 00:29:44,783
Look at
the bright side.

696
00:29:46,185 --> 00:29:48,520
[Birds squawking]

697
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:50,990
I can't believe
this is happening.

698
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:52,992
How are
we gonna get downtown?

699
00:29:53,192 --> 00:29:56,395
Damn it! Not my baby!

700
00:29:56,595 --> 00:29:57,864
Can you fix it?

701
00:29:58,064 --> 00:29:59,265
She's not going anywhere.

702
00:30:00,332 --> 00:30:01,968
What are we
gonna do now?

703
00:30:03,502 --> 00:30:05,004
I got us covered.

704
00:30:10,542 --> 00:30:12,111
Bye, old girl.

705
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:13,345
Really?

706
00:30:18,117 --> 00:30:19,318
What are you doing?

707
00:30:19,518 --> 00:30:20,920
This van was my baby.

708
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:22,021
You don't remember
your first car?

709
00:30:22,221 --> 00:30:23,990
No.

710
00:30:24,190 --> 00:30:25,391
You don't remember
your first car?

711
00:30:25,591 --> 00:30:27,026
No. Come on.
Let's go.

712
00:30:27,226 --> 00:30:28,427
Ali said that about you.

713
00:30:28,627 --> 00:30:30,329
What?
Nothing.

714
00:30:31,463 --> 00:30:32,865
Let me
just grab something.

715
00:30:33,065 --> 00:30:35,134
Well, please hurry.

716
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:44,176
Oh, my God,
Kerouac. Really?

717
00:30:44,376 --> 00:30:46,112
No.

718
00:30:52,251 --> 00:30:53,185
What was that?

719
00:30:53,385 --> 00:30:54,453
Nothing. Let's go.

720
00:31:04,563 --> 00:31:05,965
I gave her this.

721
00:31:11,103 --> 00:31:12,204
Which one,
you think?

722
00:31:12,404 --> 00:31:14,206
We're going
to steal a car?

723
00:31:14,406 --> 00:31:16,442
Well, if you're right,
there's not gonna be
a car left anyways.

724
00:31:16,642 --> 00:31:17,576
What if
the owners need it?

725
00:31:17,776 --> 00:31:19,278
More than we need it?

726
00:31:19,478 --> 00:31:20,947
No, no, no, no! Don't!

727
00:31:21,147 --> 00:31:22,348
This one's unlocked.

728
00:31:22,548 --> 00:31:25,017
Last thing we need
is a lacerated wrist.

729
00:31:25,217 --> 00:31:26,385
Think before
you act, please.

730
00:31:26,585 --> 00:31:27,553
Yeah, yeah.

731
00:31:35,627 --> 00:31:37,429
[Sparks crackle]

732
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:39,231
You know, if you're trying
to convince me you're

733
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:41,333
A good influence
on my stepdaughter,
it's not working.

734
00:31:42,801 --> 00:31:44,003
Look, I'm not
trying to convince you
of anything, all right?

735
00:31:44,203 --> 00:31:46,238
[Engine starts]

736
00:31:50,776 --> 00:31:51,910
All right.

737
00:32:00,052 --> 00:32:01,687
[Car horns honking]

738
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:05,457
[Echoing]
Help me!

739
00:32:05,657 --> 00:32:07,093
Anyone!

740
00:32:07,293 --> 00:32:09,161
We're in the elevator!

741
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:10,963
Sweetheart, sweetheart,
look at me.

742
00:32:11,163 --> 00:32:13,966
Look at me.
You're going to be
all right.

743
00:32:14,166 --> 00:32:15,467
Cough. Cough.
It helps. Cough.

744
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:17,503
Take deep breaths,
Arnold.

745
00:32:17,703 --> 00:32:19,338
Arnie,
please don't leave me!

746
00:32:19,538 --> 00:32:21,440
Please stay with me.

747
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:23,542
Sir, sir, hand me
my purse, please.

748
00:32:23,742 --> 00:32:25,211
I think there's
some aspirin in it.

749
00:32:25,411 --> 00:32:27,046
I think it could help.

750
00:32:27,246 --> 00:32:29,948
* Let me call you
sweetheart *

751
00:32:30,149 --> 00:32:34,253
* I'm in love with you *

752
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,595
Damn it. The network
is completely down.

753
00:32:43,795 --> 00:32:47,966
I have no idea how
that activity affected
the prediction model.

754
00:32:48,167 --> 00:32:49,368
Take Canyon Road.

755
00:32:49,568 --> 00:32:52,138
Canyon Road?
That'll take forever.

756
00:32:52,338 --> 00:32:54,673
You think the freeways
are gonna be any faster?

757
00:32:54,873 --> 00:32:56,008
[Sighs]

758
00:32:59,378 --> 00:33:01,547
I just want you to know

759
00:33:01,747 --> 00:33:03,282
I'm not seeing
any other girls.

760
00:33:03,482 --> 00:33:06,018
I thought you weren't
trying to convince me.

761
00:33:06,218 --> 00:33:07,686
I'm committed to Ali.

762
00:33:07,886 --> 00:33:09,488
Well, if you were
so committed to her,

763
00:33:09,688 --> 00:33:11,557
Why did you convince her
to drop out of school?

764
00:33:11,757 --> 00:33:13,292
What makes you think
that was my idea?

765
00:33:13,492 --> 00:33:15,661
And that tattoo? I bet
that was your idea as well.

766
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:17,663
God, you really
don't know Ali, do you?

767
00:33:17,863 --> 00:33:21,733
Look, she
