00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:36,186
Bus is full!
Copy that.

1274
00:57:36,921 --> 00:57:37,988
Sir, the bus
is full.

1275
00:57:38,422 --> 00:57:38,889
What?

1276
00:57:39,089 --> 00:57:40,725
Wait. Is there...

1277
00:57:40,925 --> 00:57:42,527
Is there
another bus coming?

1278
00:57:42,727 --> 00:57:43,928
I doubt it.
Next best option

1279
00:57:44,128 --> 00:57:45,530
Is a bomb shelter
on Flower.

1280
00:57:52,803 --> 00:57:56,106
A general evacuation has been
given to Los Angeles and all

1281
00:57:56,306 --> 00:57:58,909
Of the surrounding outlying
areas. Pretty much anyone

1282
00:57:59,109 --> 00:58:02,046
West of the San Andreas
fault line must evacuate.

1283
00:58:02,246 --> 00:58:05,983
A major catastrophic earthquake
event has been predicted

1284
00:58:06,183 --> 00:58:09,620
To strike downtown
Los Angeles at any minute.

1285
00:58:13,658 --> 00:58:14,992
Shit!

1286
00:58:15,192 --> 00:58:16,026
They're
detaining people.

1287
00:58:17,161 --> 00:58:18,596
Hey, you guys
can't be here!

1288
00:58:18,796 --> 00:58:19,597
We're
evacuating!

1289
00:58:19,797 --> 00:58:20,765
Ah, we're so close.

1290
00:58:22,232 --> 00:58:23,868
What do we do?
What do we do?

1291
00:58:24,068 --> 00:58:24,869
Tunnels.

1292
00:58:28,305 --> 00:58:29,740
Sewer?
No, Prohibition tunnels.

1293
00:58:29,940 --> 00:58:31,776
I used to run
all up and down them.

1294
00:58:31,976 --> 00:58:32,943
They're famous.
Okay, where?

1295
00:58:33,143 --> 00:58:34,845
Um, okay, follow me.
Okay.

1296
00:58:36,914 --> 00:58:38,616
The entrance
is over here!

1297
00:58:40,985 --> 00:58:43,788
What if your data is off
and it hits early?

1298
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:45,556
Then we're
crushed alive. And?

1299
00:58:54,932 --> 00:58:57,067
The hotel is
about five blocks away.

1300
00:58:57,267 --> 00:58:58,936
The tunnel runs
right under it.

1301
00:59:00,204 --> 00:59:01,806
Keep moving.
Keep moving. Keep moving.

1302
00:59:04,742 --> 00:59:05,876
Careful for this wire.

1303
00:59:06,076 --> 00:59:07,845
Might have
some electricity in it.

1304
00:59:08,045 --> 00:59:09,179
This is crazy.

1305
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:11,548
You sure
you know your way
around down here?

1306
00:59:12,983 --> 00:59:14,919
Just trust me.
Watch your step.

1307
00:59:35,172 --> 00:59:37,574
No going back now anyway.
Let's go.

1308
00:59:40,044 --> 00:59:41,111
Whoa.

1309
00:59:42,312 --> 00:59:43,347
What?

1310
00:59:43,547 --> 00:59:44,348
Oh, no.

1311
00:59:45,115 --> 00:59:45,850
Oh, my God. What happened?

1312
00:59:46,817 --> 00:59:47,284
Well, he didn't
die in the quake.

1313
00:59:48,118 --> 00:59:48,653
There's no sign
of trauma.

1314
00:59:49,453 --> 00:59:50,087
Looks like
he just died.

1315
00:59:50,688 --> 00:59:51,656
What killed him?

1316
00:59:52,723 --> 00:59:54,659
Oh, no.

1317
00:59:54,859 --> 00:59:56,861
Same thing
that's corroding
this penny.

1318
00:59:58,395 --> 01:00:00,798
Hydrogen sulfide.

1319
01:00:00,998 --> 01:00:03,834
Earthquake must
have caused a leak.
[coughs]

1320
01:00:04,034 --> 01:00:05,803
This poor guy
must have been
just down here working

1321
01:00:06,003 --> 01:00:07,037
When he got overcome.

1322
01:00:07,237 --> 01:00:08,138
Is it explosive?

1323
01:00:08,338 --> 01:00:09,840
Very.
[coughing]

1324
01:00:10,040 --> 01:00:11,108
That means...

1325
01:00:11,308 --> 01:00:13,110
We're in big trouble.
Come on.

1326
01:00:18,115 --> 01:00:20,050
[Both coughing]

1327
01:00:21,986 --> 01:00:23,620
I'm so dizzy.
Keep going!

1328
01:00:23,821 --> 01:00:24,855
Ah, careful!

1329
01:00:26,891 --> 01:00:28,125
Damn it.

1330
01:00:33,964 --> 01:00:36,300
[Both coughing]

1331
01:00:40,537 --> 01:00:43,808
Help me move this.
We've got to clear
an opening.

1332
01:00:48,212 --> 01:00:51,081
[Both coughing]

1333
01:00:51,281 --> 01:00:52,883
I'm gonna pass out.

1334
01:00:54,418 --> 01:00:55,820
I can't go on.

1335
01:00:56,020 --> 01:00:58,789
We've got to.
Help me.

1336
01:00:58,989 --> 01:01:00,357
Ah, I'm getting
so dizzy.

1337
01:01:02,459 --> 01:01:04,394
[Sirens blaring]

1338
01:01:08,165 --> 01:01:10,100
[Coughs]

1339
01:01:11,802 --> 01:01:13,938
Hey, Ali, this one's
just for you, kiddo.

1340
01:01:14,138 --> 01:01:15,740
We're trying
to make it out to you,

1341
01:01:15,940 --> 01:01:17,808
But it's not looking
really good at this point,

1342
01:01:18,008 --> 01:01:19,376
So...

1343
01:01:21,011 --> 01:01:23,080
I need you to stay safe.

1344
01:01:25,015 --> 01:01:26,683
Stay in that hotel.

1345
01:01:28,118 --> 01:01:30,020
Your father's
coming to get you.

1346
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:32,289
He's gonna get you
out of there.

1347
01:01:37,394 --> 01:01:38,796
All right, tell them!

1348
01:01:39,897 --> 01:01:41,398
Tell them I helped you!

1349
01:01:41,598 --> 01:01:43,233
I didn't have
to help you!

1350
01:01:43,433 --> 01:01:47,171
You told me
that we would make it
on that bus!

1351
01:01:47,371 --> 01:01:48,205
Sir, I understand,
but...

1352
01:01:48,405 --> 01:01:49,740
Look, it's leaving!

1353
01:01:49,940 --> 01:01:51,241
Look, I have a life!

1354
01:01:51,441 --> 01:01:53,744
Why should I
be punished for
helping them?

1355
01:01:53,944 --> 01:01:54,745
That doesn't make
any sense!

1356
01:01:54,945 --> 01:01:55,545
Sir...

1357
01:01:55,746 --> 01:01:56,881
I'm getting on that bus!

1358
01:01:57,081 --> 01:01:57,882
Sir!

1359
01:01:58,648 --> 01:01:59,016
Get your hands
off me!

1360
01:02:00,450 --> 01:02:01,385
Hey!

1361
01:02:01,585 --> 01:02:04,822
[Grunting]

1362
01:02:05,923 --> 01:02:07,391
Get your hands off me!

1363
01:02:07,591 --> 01:02:08,859
Get off me!

1364
01:02:09,059 --> 01:02:11,128
I deserve to be
on that bus!

1365
01:02:11,328 --> 01:02:13,197
Calm down, sir!
Calm down, sir!

1366
01:02:13,397 --> 01:02:14,264
Calm down!
Get off me!

1367
01:02:14,464 --> 01:02:16,100
[Gunshot]
[gasps]

1368
01:02:19,469 --> 01:02:22,439
Calm down, sir!
Calm down!

1369
01:02:28,045 --> 01:02:29,479
All right, back off.

1370
01:02:29,679 --> 01:02:32,850
You don't get to choose
who lives and who dies.

1371
01:02:33,050 --> 01:02:35,519
I was supposed to be
on that bus.

1372
01:02:35,719 --> 01:02:37,287
I helped them!

1373
01:02:41,158 --> 01:02:42,860
Well, if you
get to choose...

1374
01:02:43,928 --> 01:02:45,029
Well,
then so can I.

1375
01:02:46,130 --> 01:02:48,398
Mr. Kaplin,
please don't.

1376
01:02:49,466 --> 01:02:50,534
You used me.

1377
01:02:58,075 --> 01:02:59,176
Hank...

1378
01:03:00,377 --> 01:03:02,312
I'm just sending this
to you,

1379
01:03:02,512 --> 01:03:04,781
Because I don't want Ali
to hear or see this.

1380
01:03:04,982 --> 01:03:05,983
I don't want her to lose hope,

1381
01:03:06,183 --> 01:03:08,118
But I don't want you
to lose hope either,

1382
01:03:08,318 --> 01:03:10,454
But things are getting
really tight down here.

1383
01:03:10,654 --> 01:03:13,991
And you know I'm not the kind
that gets sentimental...

1384
01:03:16,326 --> 01:03:21,866
But I just want you
to know that I love you...

1385
01:03:24,268 --> 01:03:29,373
You big, strong,
wonderful flyboy, you.

1386
01:03:31,241 --> 01:03:34,378
You are the Orville
to my Wilbur.

1387
01:03:34,578 --> 01:03:36,380
Don't you dare say,
"Redenbacher,"

1388
01:03:36,580 --> 01:03:39,483
Because that's a stupid joke,
and I'm always saying

1389
01:03:39,683 --> 01:03:42,252
That you're too old
to be saying it, anyway.

1390
01:03:44,721 --> 01:03:47,324
But you are my husband,

1391
01:03:47,524 --> 01:03:50,895
My partner, my granite rock,

1392
01:03:51,095 --> 01:03:56,533
And I thank God
for you every day.

1393
01:03:58,702 --> 01:04:02,139
Thank you so much
for saving me.

1394
01:04:02,339 --> 01:04:04,541
You have no idea.

1395
01:04:04,741 --> 01:04:06,276
And no matter what happens,

1396
01:04:06,476 --> 01:04:09,013
There's nothing
that's going to take that away,

1397
01:04:09,213 --> 01:04:12,149
How I feel for you
and what you mean to me.

1398
01:04:14,651 --> 01:04:18,889
And if we don't get out of this
alive or together...

1399
01:04:20,324 --> 01:04:22,592
Just know that I love you.

1400
01:04:26,496 --> 01:04:28,532
I love you, Hank.

1401
01:04:30,534 --> 01:04:32,036
Go get Ali.

1402
01:04:35,239 --> 01:04:36,974
Go get our baby girl.

1403
01:04:41,278 --> 01:04:43,213
[Both coughing]

1404
01:04:45,382 --> 01:04:47,051
Ali's strong.

1405
01:04:48,218 --> 01:04:50,387
She'll make it
without us.

1406
01:04:51,788 --> 01:04:53,924
Wait.

1407
01:04:54,124 --> 01:04:55,359
Another foreshock's
coming.

1408
01:04:56,593 --> 01:04:58,128
You sure?

1409
01:04:59,196 --> 01:05:01,231
100%.

1410
01:05:01,431 --> 01:05:03,300
[Both coughing]

1411
01:05:04,301 --> 01:05:05,302
It'll crush us.

1412
01:05:05,502 --> 01:05:06,971
Probably.

1413
01:05:07,171 --> 01:05:09,940
[Debris shifting, falling]

1414
01:05:10,140 --> 01:05:12,576
[Both coughing]

1415
01:05:24,421 --> 01:05:26,123
Chevy Chevette.

1416
01:05:28,158 --> 01:05:29,159
What?

1417
01:05:30,227 --> 01:05:31,295
Electric blue

1418
01:05:31,495 --> 01:05:35,932
1977 Chevy Chevette

1419
01:05:36,133 --> 01:05:39,503
That I loved with
my whole heart.

1420
01:05:42,239 --> 01:05:44,274
That was my first car.

1421
01:05:47,711 --> 01:05:49,513
Hey!
Huh?

1422
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:52,282
Wake up.

1423
01:05:55,585 --> 01:05:58,655
[Coughing]
What?

1424
01:05:58,855 --> 01:06:00,657
I want
to tell you, Nick...

1425
01:06:04,494 --> 01:06:06,296
You're really
a solid guy.

1426
01:06:07,497 --> 01:06:09,399
I think it's safe
to say that...

1427
01:06:10,834 --> 01:06:13,570
You would
have moved Heaven
and Earth for Ali.

1428
01:06:13,770 --> 01:06:15,472
Ironic choice of words.

1429
01:06:16,706 --> 01:06:18,275
[Coughs]

1430
01:06:18,475 --> 01:06:20,177
Yes, I love Ali.

1431
01:06:21,778 --> 01:06:24,048
She could have done
a lot worse.

1432
01:06:24,248 --> 01:06:25,649
So...

1433
01:06:27,217 --> 01:06:28,485
Can we talk
about my grade now?

1434
01:06:28,685 --> 01:06:29,753
Not changing it.

1435
01:06:29,953 --> 01:06:31,655
[Chuckles]

1436
01:06:31,855 --> 01:06:33,490
Didn't think so.

1437
01:06:39,729 --> 01:06:42,132
Ferdinand was
our first kid.

1438
01:06:43,633 --> 01:06:45,469
What?

1439
01:06:46,736 --> 01:06:51,508
Ferdinand, that...
That dumb little toy.

1440
01:06:53,343 --> 01:06:54,744
Ali hated it,

1441
01:06:54,944 --> 01:06:57,381
But, uh,
she threw it away

1442
01:06:57,581 --> 01:06:59,549
Or dropped it
or something.

1443
01:07:00,917 --> 01:07:02,319
But I kept it.

1444
01:07:04,388 --> 01:07:08,092
When she found that I had it,
she made fun of me...

1445
01:07:09,393 --> 01:07:11,095
But it grew on her,

1446
01:07:11,295 --> 01:07:13,530
And she got
sentimental about it.

1447
01:07:13,730 --> 01:07:15,365
A little toy.

1448
01:07:17,767 --> 01:07:20,404
[Coughing]
Stupid.

1449
01:07:21,471 --> 01:07:23,307
It's not stupid.

1450
01:07:23,507 --> 01:07:25,709
I just wanted
to give it to her.

1451
01:07:26,910 --> 01:07:28,312
Yeah.

1452
01:07:37,321 --> 01:07:38,788
[Coughing]

1453
01:07:48,632 --> 01:07:49,699
[Gasps]

1454
01:07:51,235 --> 01:07:52,836
Nick! Air! Air!

1455
01:07:54,838 --> 01:07:58,342
I think I see the... I think
I can see a way out! Come on.

1456
01:08:06,716 --> 01:08:08,652
[Coughing]

1457
01:08:13,990 --> 01:08:15,559
I see light.

1458
01:08:17,461 --> 01:08:18,462
Fresh air.

1459
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:20,164
[Coughing]

1460
01:08:20,364 --> 01:08:21,398
Can we make it out?

1461
01:08:21,598 --> 01:08:23,167
Ah, no way.

1462
01:08:29,806 --> 01:08:32,209
Wait. I see
the way out.

1463
01:08:33,277 --> 01:08:34,744
[Coughing]

1464
01:08:38,915 --> 01:08:41,651
[Coughing]

1465
01:08:41,851 --> 01:08:43,220
Oh, no.
What?

1466
01:08:43,420 --> 01:08:44,888
There's more gas
this way.

1467
01:08:45,088 --> 01:08:47,391
[Groans]
Take a deep breath!

1468
01:08:47,591 --> 01:08:49,526
No, we can make it!

1469
01:08:49,726 --> 01:08:52,529
[Coughing]

1470
01:09:05,041 --> 01:09:07,177
[Both coughing]

1471
01:09:22,626 --> 01:09:24,294
If that sparks,
we're dead.

1472
01:09:40,744 --> 01:09:42,446
No! No!

1473
01:09:42,646 --> 01:09:44,214
Yeah, I can pick this.
Just let me

1474
01:09:44,414 --> 01:09:46,182
Look for a paper clip
or something.

1475
01:09:52,689 --> 01:09:54,824
Whoa, wait,
wait, wait, wait!
You can cause a spark!

1476
01:09:56,626 --> 01:09:57,594
Come on!

1477
01:09:57,794 --> 01:09:58,662
[Sighs]

1478
01:10:16,112 --> 01:10:17,247
Come on.

1479
01:10:33,563 --> 01:10:34,498
Calm down, sir!

1480
01:10:35,832 --> 01:10:37,967
You have a vehicle.
I know you do.

1481
01:10:38,167 --> 01:10:39,469
You give me the keys.

1482
01:10:39,669 --> 01:10:41,271
We don't.
We have specific orders

1483
01:10:41,471 --> 01:10:42,939
To rendezvous
at the bomb shelter.

1484
01:10:45,475 --> 01:10:46,943
I don't believe you.

1485
01:10:47,143 --> 01:10:48,378
Downtown L.A.

1486
01:10:48,578 --> 01:10:49,713
Is the last place

1487
01:10:49,913 --> 01:10:52,316
Anybody would
wanna be during a 10.0.

1488
01:10:52,516 --> 01:10:53,550
Now give me the keys!

1489
01:10:53,750 --> 01:10:54,718
Mr. Kaplin, I think

1490
01:10:54,918 --> 01:10:55,885
We should go
to the shelter.

1491
01:10:58,121 --> 01:10:59,523
You have a car,
don't you?

1492
01:10:59,723 --> 01:11:00,557
[Gasps]

1493
01:11:00,757 --> 01:11:01,858
Give me the keys.

1494
01:11:02,058 --> 01:11:03,427
It's too late for that.

1495
01:11:03,627 --> 01:11:04,728
I think
going to the shelter...

1496
01:11:04,928 --> 01:11:08,264
No, everything
is going to come down.

1497
01:11:08,465 --> 01:11:09,766
W-We have to try.

1498
01:11:11,668 --> 01:11:14,504
It is my turn
to get some help!

1499
01:11:24,948 --> 01:11:26,583
[Screaming]

1500
01:11:26,783 --> 01:11:28,418
[Car alarms blaring]

1501
01:11:31,621 --> 01:11:32,589
We made it!

1502
01:11:32,789 --> 01:11:34,691
I can't believe it!

1503
01:11:35,892 --> 01:11:37,293
We're not out
of the woods yet.

1504
01:11:37,494 --> 01:11:38,928
We gotta get Ali
and get to the roof!

1505
01:11:52,976 --> 01:11:54,744
MILES: Nobody move.
I will shoot.

1506
01:11:54,944 --> 01:11:57,013
You had no right to say
I couldn't be on that bus!

1507
01:11:59,115 --> 01:12:00,484
I'm gonna live.

1508
01:12:00,684 --> 01:12:01,551
No.

1509
01:12:02,652 --> 01:12:03,853
All right, get back.

1510
01:12:04,053 --> 01:12:05,389
You, get over there!

1511
01:12:05,589 --> 01:12:06,390
I'm warning you!

1512
01:12:07,491 --> 01:12:08,725
Hey!

1513
01:12:09,793 --> 01:12:10,760
Get away from her!

1514
01:12:12,095 --> 01:12:13,397
[Gunshot]

1515
01:12:13,597 --> 01:12:14,731
Ohh! Oh! No!
[gunshot]

1516
01:12:14,931 --> 01:12:16,733
No. No!

1517
01:12:16,933 --> 01:12:17,901
No, get off me!

1518
01:12:18,101 --> 01:12:19,969
I deserve to be
on that bus!

1519
01:12:20,169 --> 01:12:21,371
I helped them!

1520
01:12:21,571 --> 01:12:23,573
You don't get
to choose!

1521
01:12:24,808 --> 01:12:26,610
MITCH: I helped them!

1522
01:12:26,810 --> 01:12:27,777
No!

1523
01:12:28,845 --> 01:12:29,913
No!

1524
01:12:30,113 --> 01:12:31,381
I can't believe
you're here!

1525
01:12:31,581 --> 01:12:32,482
We have to get out!

1526
01:12:33,383 --> 01:12:33,783
No, we have to get
to the roof.

1527
01:12:34,884 --> 01:12:35,719
What? No! The place
is going to collapse!

1528
01:12:36,586 --> 01:12:36,986
People, listen!
We gotta go!

1529
01:12:37,954 --> 01:12:38,888
The bomb shelter's
two blocks away.

1530
01:12:40,023 --> 01:12:41,357
No way.
We are talking
about an M12 now.

1531
01:12:42,759 --> 01:12:43,760
Nothing within miles
of this place will
be left standing.

1532
01:12:44,594 --> 01:12:45,395
What?
Come with us, okay?

1533
01:12:46,329 --> 01:12:46,863
There's a helicopter
on the roof.

